WEBVTT

01:36.138 --> 01:38.004
<i>It's Mr. Hicks
from the school again.</i>

01:38.432 --> 01:40.424
<i>This is the third time
I've called</i>

01:40.517 --> 01:42.317
<i>about the incident
that happened this morning.</i>

01:44.396 --> 01:45.396
<i>Look,</i>

01:45.480 --> 01:47.142
<i>we both know Elijah is
a good kid.</i>

01:48.150 --> 01:49.150
<i>And...</i>

01:49.443 --> 01:51.480
<i>I know your family's
been through a lot lately,</i>

01:51.570 --> 01:54.153
<i>but I have been seeing
some changes in him</i>

01:54.239 --> 01:55.639
<i>that I'd like to
talk to you about.</i>

01:56.116 --> 01:57.116
<i>So please,</i>

01:58.827 --> 02:00.387
<i>give me a call back
as soon as you can.</i>

02:00.454 --> 02:02.161
<i>All right? Thanks. Bye.</i>

02:09.588 --> 02:10.588
I called your dad.

02:11.089 --> 02:12.089
He can't make it.

02:15.344 --> 02:16.676
Come on, I'll drive you home.

03:54.317 --> 03:55.878
<i>What's up?
You got another haul for us, or what?</i>

03:55.902 --> 03:56.902
<i>Almost there.</i>

03:57.195 --> 03:58.195
What's copper at?

03:58.780 --> 04:01.488
Copper and aluminum,
70 cents a pound this week.

05:01.802 --> 05:02.802
Hello?

05:23.114 --> 05:24.230
Anyone there?

05:30.747 --> 05:31.747
Hello?

05:48.974 --> 05:49.974
Oh, my God.

07:35.038 --> 07:36.038
Elijah.

07:37.207 --> 07:38.207
Elijah!

07:38.959 --> 07:40.075
Suspension, huh?

07:43.838 --> 07:46.581
Get your shoes on.
I need your help out back.

08:00.063 --> 08:01.770
Why you getting in fistfights, son?

08:06.569 --> 08:07.776
He was talking about Mom.

08:11.449 --> 08:12.449
Come here.

08:14.703 --> 08:15.703
Come here, sit down.

08:21.626 --> 08:22.626
You know,

08:23.795 --> 08:25.081
if I'm hard on you,

08:26.589 --> 08:27.921
it's because the world is hard.

08:29.426 --> 08:30.426
You've seen that.

08:32.511 --> 08:33.511
But this,

08:34.347 --> 08:36.554
this is not what your mom would've wanted.

08:42.856 --> 08:44.063
Come on, come on.

08:46.192 --> 08:47.478
You take my tool box.

08:50.488 --> 08:52.480
We're gonna need a third place
for dinner tonight.

08:54.075 --> 08:55.156
Your brother got out.

08:56.494 --> 08:58.030
I want you to be careful around him.

09:13.261 --> 09:14.261
Remember what I told you.

09:20.769 --> 09:21.769
El i.

09:22.896 --> 09:23.896
Man...

09:24.481 --> 09:27.098
Six years didn't seem like
such a long time until just now.

09:30.487 --> 09:31.487
You got big.

09:45.210 --> 09:46.210
Hey.

09:48.505 --> 09:49.745
This is just for a week or two.

09:51.466 --> 09:52.466
I know.

09:53.802 --> 09:54.802
Thanks.

09:59.432 --> 10:00.912
Let's go see what you did to my digs.

10:13.988 --> 10:14.988
What are those?

10:15.990 --> 10:16.901
My shoes.

10:16.991 --> 10:18.152
You wear those in public?

10:20.328 --> 10:21.614
I'm saving for new ones.

10:22.163 --> 10:24.075
With what? Dad's cheap-ass allowance?

10:26.209 --> 10:27.666
Oh, you got a little

10:28.461 --> 10:29.827
lemonade stand thing going?

10:31.673 --> 10:32.673
I can respect that.

10:37.762 --> 10:41.176
Hey, I got a pair of Chucks
hiding in a trunk around here somewhere.

10:42.142 --> 10:43.942
If I find them, you can have them.
Sound good?

10:45.937 --> 10:48.850
Cool. 'Cause those smell like shit, man.

10:56.156 --> 10:57.156
Wow.

10:59.534 --> 11:01.053
You guys wouldn't believe
how much you miss

11:01.077 --> 11:02.238
a home-cooked meal in prison.

11:04.372 --> 11:05.372
Glad you like.

11:06.249 --> 11:07.249
I do.

11:13.298 --> 11:14.298
Those are new.

11:14.924 --> 11:15.924
Yeah.

11:16.217 --> 11:17.217
You like them?

11:17.760 --> 11:18.760
These...

11:19.804 --> 11:21.136
ward off evil spirits.

11:21.806 --> 11:23.013
That one wards off Mexicans.

11:32.275 --> 11:33.275
Sorry.

11:35.111 --> 11:36.111
Just glad to be home.

11:37.363 --> 11:38.363
What's your next step?

11:39.324 --> 11:40.484
- I'm gonna get a job.
- Yeah?

11:41.618 --> 11:42.618
Doing what?

11:44.454 --> 11:45.454
Well, actually,

11:45.580 --> 11:47.391
I was hoping that you might
put in a good word for me

11:47.415 --> 11:49.095
- down at the site you're working on.
- No.

11:49.542 --> 11:50.542
Can't do that.

11:51.169 --> 11:53.582
- Why not?
- Because I can't clear an ex-con.

11:53.671 --> 11:56.071
- If you told them I was your son...
- Doesn't work that way.

12:00.428 --> 12:01.428
Great, so...

12:02.513 --> 12:05.256
- Six years, no visit, no word.
- I visited.

12:05.350 --> 12:07.012
Once, to tell me my mom was dead.

12:08.228 --> 12:09.228
Thanks, Hal.

12:10.521 --> 12:12.433
And I come home, no complaints.

12:12.774 --> 12:14.766
I just ask one small favor,

12:15.151 --> 12:17.129
and you'd rather see your own son
flipping burgers?

12:17.153 --> 12:18.360
Better than being a thief.

12:23.368 --> 12:24.859
I gotta step out, bro. I'm sorry.

12:25.954 --> 12:27.240
I got people I need to see.

12:29.874 --> 12:30.990
Don't bother waiting up.

12:50.311 --> 12:51.311
Hey.

12:52.188 --> 12:53.804
Jimmy. Taylor told me to come through.

13:17.046 --> 13:18.378
He's got this bag on his head.

13:19.090 --> 13:21.360
They got the shovel, right?
Because they're gonna, you know...

13:21.384 --> 13:22.545
Afterwards, right?

13:23.011 --> 13:24.673
He swings back, hits...

13:25.263 --> 13:26.970
Hey, Solinski!

13:27.849 --> 13:28.930
Welcome home, my man.

13:30.310 --> 13:31.517
Remember my brother, Dutch?

13:31.853 --> 13:32.853
Yeah.

13:32.979 --> 13:33.979
How's it going?

13:37.984 --> 13:38.984
That's Remy.

13:39.360 --> 13:41.101
Don't worry about him, he's in a time-out.

13:41.612 --> 13:43.148
Tay, man, come on.

13:43.364 --> 13:44.980
Stick your nose back in that corner.

13:45.783 --> 13:46.983
That is, if you wanna keep it.

13:47.910 --> 13:49.697
Contemplate that shitty attitude.

13:50.997 --> 13:51.997
So, Jimmy...

13:52.665 --> 13:54.657
You wanna burn one
or just get right to it?

13:55.877 --> 13:58.119
I'm good, I don't wanna take up
any of your time.

13:59.339 --> 14:00.580
I just came by to say

14:01.299 --> 14:03.006
that I know I owe you guys some money.

14:03.426 --> 14:05.713
And I'm taking that real serious.

14:05.803 --> 14:07.635
Good. 'Cause protection ain't cheap.

14:09.349 --> 14:10.590
Dutch, what's he into us for?

14:11.017 --> 14:12.017
Sixty?

14:17.523 --> 14:18.523
You don't got our 60?

14:19.776 --> 14:20.776
No.

14:22.820 --> 14:25.153
No, but I just wanted you guys to know
I'm not dodging you.

14:26.074 --> 14:27.074
Man.

14:28.284 --> 14:29.570
That is a bummer.

14:32.038 --> 14:33.038
You see, Jimmy,

14:33.790 --> 14:35.201
me and my brother, we don't...

14:36.250 --> 14:38.492
We don't project any illusions about

14:38.961 --> 14:40.873
who we are or what we do, you know?

14:41.506 --> 14:44.874
We were very clear that first day,
post-charges or what have you,

14:45.635 --> 14:47.467
about how we deal with loans.

14:48.846 --> 14:49.846
Because,

14:50.848 --> 14:52.589
there are people who do business like you.

14:55.645 --> 14:58.012
And there's people
that do business like us.

14:58.523 --> 14:59.523
So...

15:00.441 --> 15:02.294
Is there something funny
about the language on that

15:02.318 --> 15:03.434
you didn't understand?

15:04.612 --> 15:07.195
Some kind of... fine print problem?

15:07.281 --> 15:08.281
No.

15:10.284 --> 15:11.284
No.

15:11.702 --> 15:12.702
Because,

15:13.621 --> 15:16.329
we know you have a father.
What's his name, Harold?

15:17.250 --> 15:19.492
And that... little colored brother,
too, right?

15:21.337 --> 15:22.337
I got that right?

15:22.880 --> 15:23.996
Yeah. Yeah.

15:25.299 --> 15:27.291
I mean, I guess
we can go collect from them.

15:27.510 --> 15:28.550
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Hang on.

15:29.595 --> 15:31.552
Hang on. I was just saying
I didn't have it here.

15:33.808 --> 15:35.015
I didn't say I don't have it.

15:40.648 --> 15:41.648
Okay, then.

16:27.737 --> 16:28.737
What?

16:28.946 --> 16:30.733
They... They were right here.

18:07.920 --> 18:08.920
Have a good night.

18:18.848 --> 18:19.848
Jimmy,

18:20.016 --> 18:21.016
I wanna help you.

18:22.184 --> 18:23.184
I really do.

18:25.521 --> 18:26.921
But you gotta understand something.

18:28.774 --> 18:30.015
'Cause you've got a decade

18:30.818 --> 18:32.810
of bad decisions under your belt.

18:35.823 --> 18:38.531
You're gonna have to work
at some jobs that you don't like.

18:40.995 --> 18:44.079
You have to gain experience.
You're gonna have to gain trust.

18:50.504 --> 18:52.166
Now, I'll talk to you tomorrow.

18:56.802 --> 18:58.088
No, we should talk now.

19:05.603 --> 19:06.639
60K.

19:08.356 --> 19:09.722
I need $60,000.

19:09.815 --> 19:11.793
I didn't want to ask you,
but I've got no other options.

19:11.817 --> 19:14.810
What? $60,000?
I don't have that kind of money.

19:14.904 --> 19:17.442
- Look, you gotta hear me out, okay.
- No, no, I don't.

19:17.531 --> 19:18.988
No. Not in my house.

19:19.075 --> 19:22.034
- Whatever it is, I'm not interested.
- There's a safe in your office.

19:24.205 --> 19:26.948
Please, I will never ask you
for anything ever again.

19:27.375 --> 19:29.241
- I swear.
- You want me to steal for you?

19:29.835 --> 19:31.076
Let you steal, what's this?

19:31.170 --> 19:32.810
- This isn't for me.
- Who's it for, then?

19:33.381 --> 19:34.917
- Who?
- Dangerous people.

19:35.007 --> 19:36.873
People you can't just not pay back.

19:37.301 --> 19:38.963
These guys kept me alive in jail.

19:39.220 --> 19:41.260
If I don't pay them back,
who knows what they'll do.

19:41.430 --> 19:42.870
Do you understand what I'm trying...

19:43.099 --> 19:44.635
I'm trying to help you guys.

19:44.892 --> 19:45.928
You get out of my house.

19:46.018 --> 19:47.538
- Get out of my house. Out.
- Dad. Dad.

19:48.396 --> 19:49.396
Dad.

19:52.692 --> 19:54.492
You know, I really hoped
I was gonna come back

19:54.527 --> 19:56.268
to the house that time forgot, but...

19:57.863 --> 19:59.104
you've made some changes.

20:02.284 --> 20:03.650
My room, that's gone.

20:04.578 --> 20:07.116
You got your replacement son
sleeping up there in my bed.

20:13.379 --> 20:14.995
You've erased every trace of me.

20:18.467 --> 20:19.907
What do you think Mom would've said?

20:20.720 --> 20:21.920
Don't you talk about your mom.

20:23.556 --> 20:24.797
Now you get out of my house.

20:26.600 --> 20:27.760
I'm not gonna tell you again.

20:45.077 --> 20:46.077
Here's a list.

20:46.287 --> 20:47.653
Things I need done today.

20:48.247 --> 20:49.247
All of this?

20:49.290 --> 20:50.451
Before I get home.

20:51.584 --> 20:54.201
You don't go to school, you work for me.

21:17.568 --> 21:18.568
Look at this guy.

21:19.737 --> 21:20.737
He's a chump.

21:21.530 --> 21:22.530
You say something?

21:23.407 --> 21:24.864
You trying to hurt my family?

21:59.735 --> 22:00.735
What is this?

22:02.446 --> 22:05.359
Well, there's a bunch of old scrapyards
that pay money for...

22:05.449 --> 22:06.449
You're scrapping now?

22:08.285 --> 22:09.285
Where?

22:09.745 --> 22:11.327
Just this place off Grand River.

22:11.539 --> 22:12.539
Does this place...

22:13.207 --> 22:15.665
Does it have a fence around it
and a locked gate?

22:15.751 --> 22:17.431
Does it have a sign that says, "Stay out"?

22:18.295 --> 22:19.295
Huh?

22:19.755 --> 22:20.755
Yes.

22:21.340 --> 22:22.205
All right.

22:22.299 --> 22:25.087
I've got a list of property developers
at my office

22:25.719 --> 22:27.335
that you and I are gonna go down there,

22:27.680 --> 22:31.424
and you are gonna call each
and every single one of these places...

22:31.517 --> 22:33.133
Dad, it's just a bunch of old metal.

22:33.227 --> 22:34.559
It's not yours, Elijah.

22:36.063 --> 22:37.063
None of it.

22:38.399 --> 22:39.399
Go get in the truck.

22:40.067 --> 22:41.837
- Dad, I didn't...
- Do I call the police? What?

22:41.861 --> 22:42.861
What am I gonna do?

22:45.948 --> 22:46.948
No.

22:50.870 --> 22:53.203
It was just stuff
that's been sitting there for years.

22:53.873 --> 22:56.411
Everything that has ever been stolen

22:56.500 --> 22:58.366
was something that was just sitting there.

23:01.672 --> 23:03.192
I don't even know why I listen to you.

23:03.757 --> 23:05.373
You don't have a choice in that, kid.

23:05.467 --> 23:07.254
- I'm your father.
- No, you're not.

23:08.512 --> 23:10.365
The only reason I'm here
is because you guys wanted

23:10.389 --> 23:12.472
some kind of replacement kid.

23:24.028 --> 23:25.028
Look at me.

23:28.532 --> 23:30.273
You are nobody's replacement.

23:32.870 --> 23:33.986
Your mother is...

23:34.622 --> 23:36.033
She's not here anymore.

23:37.041 --> 23:39.704
But you are our son.

23:41.045 --> 23:43.708
And now it is my job to raise you right.

23:46.342 --> 23:49.551
And I am doing the best job that I can

23:50.429 --> 23:51.465
without her.

23:55.768 --> 23:56.849
I love you, son,

23:57.603 --> 23:58.810
and that's why we're here.

24:31.136 --> 24:32.136
Stay in the truck.

24:52.324 --> 24:53.360
- Dad?
- "Dad?"

24:53.450 --> 24:55.533
Shit. Look, you can't be here.
You gotta turn around.

24:55.619 --> 24:56.619
This is Dad?

24:56.787 --> 24:58.528
Whoa, whoa, hold on. You gotta leave.

24:58.831 --> 24:59.831
Hey, Dad.

25:00.332 --> 25:02.449
- Hang on, man.
- What are you doing in here?

25:03.627 --> 25:05.539
We're just taking the money
out of this safe.

25:06.755 --> 25:08.395
Dad, you gotta get out of here right now.

25:08.674 --> 25:09.674
Just turn around,

25:10.050 --> 25:11.416
just walk out of here, trust me.

25:11.510 --> 25:14.924
I don't know what my son promised you,

25:15.014 --> 25:19.008
but that is not his to give,
and it is not yours to take.

25:19.935 --> 25:20.935
It isn't?

25:21.228 --> 25:22.685
- No.
- Taylor, please, man,

25:22.771 --> 25:24.082
- this doesn't have anything...
- Jimmy.

25:24.106 --> 25:25.291
It's got nothing to do
with him, all right?

25:25.315 --> 25:26.396
Your father was talking.

25:29.278 --> 25:30.278
Please. You were saying?

25:31.405 --> 25:33.021
I don't have a gripe with you.

25:35.868 --> 25:37.308
But we gotta put all the money back?

25:38.996 --> 25:39.996
You do.

25:40.998 --> 25:42.358
- All right, hang on.
- No, look...

25:43.459 --> 25:44.459
I love this part.

25:51.633 --> 25:52.669
Please, Dad.

26:00.100 --> 26:01.100
No, no!

26:12.613 --> 26:14.275
Dutch. Dutch.

26:18.452 --> 26:19.943
Dad. Dad.

26:21.288 --> 26:22.870
Dad, Dad, hold on, hold on.

26:25.000 --> 26:26.207
No, no, no, no.

26:51.110 --> 26:52.110
Shit!

27:02.246 --> 27:03.306
- What's up?
- What are you doing?

27:03.330 --> 27:04.696
Where's... Where's Dad?

27:27.813 --> 27:29.224
You see that chain that was broken?

27:29.690 --> 27:30.690
- No.
- At the...

27:31.441 --> 27:32.441
At the south gate?

27:33.235 --> 27:34.235
Yeah.

27:34.486 --> 27:36.227
These guys broke in and they...

27:36.780 --> 27:39.864
dumped over a whole shit-ton
of concrete back there.

27:39.950 --> 27:42.158
And he called you to pick me up?

27:42.244 --> 27:44.201
Yeah. Yeah, why wouldn't he?

27:45.956 --> 27:47.618
Well, I heard you two arguing last night.

27:48.417 --> 27:49.417
Yeah?

27:51.295 --> 27:52.295
How much did you hear?

27:52.796 --> 27:54.076
Well, he was kind of pissed off.

27:54.464 --> 27:55.671
I heard him kick you out.

27:55.924 --> 27:57.631
Yeah. We're family, that shit happens.

27:58.927 --> 28:01.010
Well, why are you so sweaty?

28:01.680 --> 28:02.680
Huh?

28:04.683 --> 28:06.094
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah.

28:07.477 --> 28:08.477
Yeah, it's fine, man.

28:52.940 --> 28:53.940
Guess so.

28:56.068 --> 28:57.068
Yeah.

28:58.654 --> 28:59.654
He's here.

29:02.532 --> 29:03.532
You wanna talk to him?

29:04.910 --> 29:06.276
All right, yeah. Sounds good.

29:07.287 --> 29:08.287
Bye.

29:10.791 --> 29:11.791
What?

29:13.085 --> 29:15.005
Sounds like it's a real shit-show
out there, man.

29:15.504 --> 29:17.245
That spill's gonna take
a week to clean up.

29:17.506 --> 29:18.587
Round-the-clock shifts.

29:19.549 --> 29:21.211
He said something about after-school...

29:22.010 --> 29:23.046
- Daycare.
- Daycare?

29:23.804 --> 29:26.217
- I'm 14, I'm not six.
- I told him, I told him.

29:30.143 --> 29:31.429
We gotta pull together, dude.

29:34.439 --> 29:36.522
I mean, I know I've been away
for a long time.

29:38.193 --> 29:39.900
And you've been busy
with school and stuff.

29:39.987 --> 29:41.023
I got suspended.

29:41.238 --> 29:42.238
No shit?

29:42.864 --> 29:44.400
Well, even more reason, then.

29:45.409 --> 29:46.409
For what?

29:46.785 --> 29:48.505
I told Dad that we should go
on a road trip.

29:48.829 --> 29:49.829
Me, you, and him.

29:50.289 --> 29:53.373
Well, just me and you at first,
but he'll come find us later.

29:54.084 --> 29:55.165
We could go out west.

29:55.252 --> 29:56.252
Lake Tahoe.

29:56.962 --> 29:58.043
Mom loved it out there.

29:59.006 --> 30:00.646
Hey, it's gotta be warmer than here, man.

30:07.222 --> 30:08.679
And Dad's okay with this?

30:09.433 --> 30:11.015
Yeah. He's fine with it. I called him.

30:11.101 --> 30:12.933
You wanna talk to him? Call him.

30:19.693 --> 30:21.933
Look, you wanna have an adventure
or you wanna do chores?

30:24.406 --> 30:25.406
I know what I'm doing.

30:29.995 --> 30:30.995
Great.

30:31.079 --> 30:32.079
Go pack some shit.

30:32.164 --> 30:33.621
- Now?
- We're out of here in 10.

30:52.392 --> 30:54.054
Come on, come on, come on.

30:56.480 --> 30:58.062
Yo. All right, you ready?

30:58.565 --> 30:59.565
Give me that bag.

31:00.067 --> 31:01.067
Nice.

31:01.526 --> 31:02.966
Did you put your whole room in here?

31:04.738 --> 31:05.738
All right, jump in.

31:06.031 --> 31:07.031
Let's go, come on.

31:43.193 --> 31:44.193
Toss this shit.

32:10.637 --> 32:11.844
Hey, there he is.

32:13.390 --> 32:15.222
Rise and shine, welcome to Iowa.

32:17.602 --> 32:19.594
Man, I'm starving.
How about some breakfast?

32:58.852 --> 33:00.388
By the time we came of age,

33:00.812 --> 33:03.646
the game to beat down on Klinger Street...

33:05.567 --> 33:07.149
This fella named Big Reggie.

33:10.238 --> 33:11.238
Never forget...

33:12.324 --> 33:14.065
the day Big Reg

33:14.659 --> 33:16.446
decided to lay claim to my Walkman.

33:19.080 --> 33:20.946
I came home crying and bleeding.

33:21.917 --> 33:23.909
When he saw the state I was in,
before I knew it,

